I just read up on the thread on the positive effects Vietnam Vets, and saw some good posts there.  Cook, the above post was well worth the replay.  Thanks.<br><br>
I too have thought that some of the positive effects come through our kids.  This is where we interact with society, and where we have a great effect.  What I've seen is an increased committment to kids by sowe Vietnam Vets.  Those who where mentioned above by MTF probably haven't been much involved with families, and probably did not product many children.  This may or may not be true, but it is my experience.<br><br>
I cannot speak of others, but I know that my kids are the most important people in my universe.  The more we can do to prepare them for a future much different than ours, the better.
